<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>take someone away • take someone off</xh5><p> <i>take someone away—</i>take smb. to another place; lead a person away: The prisoner was <u>taken away</u> by an armed guard.</p><p><i>take someone off—</i>1. <i>= take someone away:</i> Before long the young prisoner was <u>taken off</u> for questioning. 2. rescue a person from a sinking ship: Before the ship sank, all the passengers were safely <u>taken off</u>. 3. <i>(Sport)</i> remove a player: The captain decided to <u>take Snow off</u> and try a slower bowler.</p> </entry>
